        {
            "title": "Bitcoin steady as US GDP grows in Q2; Ethereum, XRP, Dogecoin drop. Bitcoin: $111,770.58, Ethereum: $4,453.39, XRP: $2.94, Dogecoin: $0.2200. ETH struggles below $4,500. US GDP on blockchain. $250 million liquidated in crypto, Bitcoin's market dominance down to 57.5%. Top Binance traders reduced long exposure to Bitcoin. Market sentiment neutral.",
            "id": "3b910383-4eba-4751-9709-5b8effed89cc",
            "description": "Bitcoin remained stable while major altcoins like Ethereum, XRP, and Dogecoin saw losses, despite the U.S. economy showing strong results in Q2. As of 9:20 p.m. ET, Bitcoin was at $111,770.58 (+0.19%), Ethereum at $4,453.39 (-1.26%), XRP at $2.94 (-0.98%), Solana at $213.18 (+4.23%), and Dogecoin at $0.2200 (-0.14%). Ethereum's market dominance grew to 13.9%, surpassing Bitcoin's 57.5%. The U.S. government put GDP figures on the blockchain, aiming to establish the country as the \"crypto capital.\" The market witnessed over $250 million in liquidations in 24 hours, with long liquidations comprising over 60%. Bitcoin's open interest increased 0.30%, although top Binance traders reduced their long exposure to Bitcoin. Market sentiment was \"Neutral.\"",
